        // 2. The number of coders available (c)
        // 3. The number of mathematicians available (m)
        // This is because each team must have at least one coder and at least one mathematician.
        // So, the number of teams cannot exceed c, nor m.
        // Also, each team requires 3 members, so the total number of teams cannot exceed (c + m + x) / 3.
        // Therefore, the maximum number of teams is min(c, m, (c + m + x) / 3).

