            // In this case, it moves left to `h[current_h_idx] - T`. The range covered is `[h[current_h_idx] - 2T, h[current_h_idx]]`.
            // So `p[current_p_idx]` must be in `[h[current_h_idx] - 2T, h[current_h_idx]]`.

            // This is getting complicated. Let's simplify.
            // We need to cover `p[current_p_idx]`.
            // We must use some head `h[current_h_idx]` (or later).
            // This head `h[current_h_idx]` must be able to reach some position `x` such that `p[current_p_idx]` is in `[x-T, x+T]`.
            // The cost to move `h[current_h_idx]` to `x` is `abs(h[current_h_idx] - x)`.
